# Using SDG11_ORCHESTRATOR_V3

The orchestrator is the main entry point for executing the UrbanGrowthSDG11 processing workflow.

## Basic Execution

Run the complete workflow:

```bash
python scripts/SDG11_ORCHESTRATOR_V3.py
```

---

## Process a Specific Year

```bash
python scripts/SDG11_ORCHESTRATOR_V3.py \
    --year 2011
```

---

## Run Selected Steps

Execute only specific workflow stages:

```bash
python scripts/SDG11_ORCHESTRATOR_V3.py \
    --year 2011 \
    --steps parse,merge,deduplicate
```

Example:

```bash
python scripts/SDG11_ORCHESTRATOR_V3.py \
    --year 2011 \
    --steps uid,gis_match,aggregate
```

---

## Available Workflow Steps

The following processing modules can be executed individually or as part of the complete workflow:

| Step | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `parse` | Parse agency listings and extract structured records |
| `merge` | Merge outputs from multiple agencies into a consolidated dataset |
| `deduplicate` | Identify and remove duplicate listings |
| `word_filter` | Apply keyword-based filtering rules |
| `uid` | Assign unique identifiers to records |
| `clean_neighborhoods` | Standardize and clean neighborhood names |
| `ptype_fix` | Normalize property-type classifications |
| `filter_records` | Remove records that fail validation criteria |
| `gis_match` | Match listings to GIS neighborhood layers |
| `unmatched_check` | Review unmatched neighborhoods and GIS failures |
| `price_standardize` | Standardize prices and monetary fields |
| `transaction_validate` | Validate transaction types (SALE / RENT) |
| `area_standardize` | Convert and standardize area measurements |
| `aggregate` | Generate neighborhood-level summary statistics |

